## check python version
```bash
py -0
```

### Note: Must be Python 3.10

---

## Create Or Switch Django project
```Bash
py -3.10  -m venv venv
```

---

venv\Scripts\activate is a command used on Windows to turn on a Python virtual environment.
```Bash
venv\Scripts\activate
```

## Install required libraries
```Bash
pip install django deepface numpy
```

## Install Opencv-python
```
pip install opencv-python==4.9.0.80
```

## Create Django project
```bash
django-admin startproject config .
```

## Create app
```Bash
python manage.py startapp users
```

## Register app in Django
```bash
config/settings.py
```

## Run server
```Bash
python manage.py runserver
```
## Install tensorflow 
```Bash
pip install tensorflow==2.15.0
```

## Install Keras
```Bash
pip install keras==2.15.0

pip install tf-keras
```